        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The &amp;quot;Planning for Best Livestock Keeper&amp;#39;s Award Function&amp;quot; scheme introduced by the Agriculture, Farmers Welfare and Cooperation Department, Gujarat, aims to encourage and recognize the contributions of dedicated pastoralists across Gujarat. Awards are distributed at the Taluka, District, and State levels during designated programs. Award winners are not eligible to apply again for the next three years.\n",
        "benefits_md": "&gt; **Taluka Level Awards (Total 496):**\n\n\n  - First Prize: ₹20,000/-\n  - Second Prize: ₹10,000/-\n\n&gt; **District Level Awards (Total 66):**\n\n\n  - First Prize: ₹25,000/-\n  - Second Prize: ₹20,000/-\n\n&gt; **State Level Awards (Total 3):**\n\n\n  - First Prize: ₹1,00,000/-\n  - Second Prize: ₹51,000/-\n  - Third Prize: ₹31,000/-\n\n&gt; **Note:** Award is given once in three years only.\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The \"Planning for Best Livestock Keeper's Award Function\" scheme by the Agriculture, Farmers Welfare and Cooperation Department honors outstanding pastoralists in Gujarat by awarding them at Taluka, District, and State levels for their excellence in animal husbandry.\n\n",
